"title": "5427: nomads",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5427",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>People who moved about from place to place, having no settled abode. They lived in tents and frequented desert places</h2>\n<h2>Examples of nomads</h2>\n<h3>The patriarchs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:12-Ps105:13\">PSA 105:12–105:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:9\">HEB 11:8–11:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:8\">GEN 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:3\">GEN 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:15\">GEN 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:18\">GEN 13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:25\">GEN 26:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:25\">GEN 31:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:21\">GEN 35:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:5\">DEU 26:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:18-1Chr16:20\">1CH 16:18–16:20</a></p>\n<h3>Israel during her desert wanderings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:13\">NUM 32:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:5-1Chr17:6\">1CH 17:5–17:6</a> <em>The Tabernacle was designed as a place of worship during this nomadic existence.</em></p>\n<h3>Other nomadic peoples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:20\">GEN 4:20</a> <em>Jabal</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:17\">JDG 4:17</a> <em>the Kenites</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:3\">JDG 6:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:7\">HAB 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps120:5\">PSA 120:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:28-Jer49:29\">JER 49:28–49:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek25:4\">EZK 25:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:20\">ISA 13:20</a> <em>Arabs</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:1-Jer35:11\">JER 35:1–35:11</a> <em>The Recabites retained their nomadic ways long after Israel had settled in the land of Canaan.</em></p>\n<h3>Desert tracks followed by nomads</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:11\">JDG 8:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:2\">JER 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>The nomadic life as a spiritual symbol</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:13-Heb11:16\">HEB 11:13–11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:17\">1PE 1:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as a nomad</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:20\">MAT 8:20</a></p>",
